				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>|This is a Cosmology Series.|</p>
<p><strong>Into</strong></p>
<p>I will briefly explain the important issues on the evolution of the background and perturbations of the universe.<br />
This is a general introduction to the evolution of the universe. It is so general that all the information can be summarized into one figure. (Actually I used two to make it more clear. The figures are extracted from the notes of <a href="http://www.astro.caltech.edu/~george/ay127/Ay127_Perturb.pdf" target="_blank">George@Caltech</a>.)</p>
<p>Here are the two figures.<br />
<div id="attachment_1947" style="width: 510px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://multiverse.lamost.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/1.jpg"><img src="http://multiverse.lamost.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/1-300x228.jpg" alt="{Cosmology}Background" title="{Cosmology}Background" width="500"  class="size-medium wp-image-1947" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">{Cosmology}Background</p></div><br />
<div id="attachment_1948" style="width: 510px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://multiverse.lamost.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/2.jpg"><img src="http://multiverse.lamost.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/2-300x229.jpg" alt="{Cosmology}Perturbations" title="{Cosmology}Perturbations" width="500"  class="size-medium wp-image-1948" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">{Cosmology}Perturbations</p></div></p>
<p>Go on reading with <a href="http://multiverse.lamost.org/blog/?p=1959">http://multiverse.lamost.org/blog/?p=1959</a>.</p>
<p>|Details will be given in the following posts.|</p>
